{% block content %}
<article class="fund-wrap fund-wrap--narrow">

  <p class="fund-eyebrow">OIATC program</p>
  <h1>Anokii: sovereign community infrastructure</h1>
  <p class="fund-lede">Community platforms built on Waaseyaa and designed to be Nation-governed, where governance and access control are structural rather than bolted on. Communities are vantage points on one shared map, not silos.</p>

  <div class="fund-body">
    <p>Anokii is designed to give a Nation a grounded, cited assistant and a resource map it governs itself, on infrastructure under community control, so a Nation's data stays home. The two vantages running today are OIATC-run demonstrations of what that looks like, seeded from public information; no Nation governs them yet. The framework underneath is built to record consent as data and keep an audit trail of every access and change.</p>
    <p>The thinking behind this program is set out in OIATC's position on AI sovereignty, <a href="/positions/sovereign-ai">when a foreign order can switch off your AI</a>: the model is the swappable layer, and the data and infrastructure a community owns are the parts that confer sovereignty.</p>
  </div>

  <section class="fund-sec">
    <h2>The work, by stage</h2>
    <ul class="fund-links">
      <li><span class="fund-stage fund-stage--proto">Prototype</span> <a href="/anokii">The Anokii instance</a> <span>· one shared map, per-community vantages, OIATC-run</span></li>
      <li><span class="fund-stage fund-stage--proto">Prototype</span> <a href="/anokii/sagamok">Sagamok vantage</a> <span>· a demonstration built from public information, not Sagamok's official platform</span></li>
      <li><span class="fund-stage fund-stage--proto">Prototype</span> <a href="/anokii/massey">Massey vantage</a> <span>· the solar project in local context, from public information</span></li>
      <li><span class="fund-stage fund-stage--live">Live</span> <a href="/explainers/where-your-data-lives">Where your data lives</a> <span>· why sovereign infrastructure matters</span></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="fund-sec">
    <h2>The fundable next step</h2>
    <div class="fund-body">
      <p>Two OIATC-run reference vantages are running. The next step is regional coverage along the North Shore, from Sault Ste. Marie to Sudbury to Manitoulin, so more Nations have a community-governed platform instead of a vendor-run one. This is the Northern Ontario technology-capacity story, and it scales one vantage at a time.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="fund-ask">
      <span class="fund-ask__amt">Regional rollout</span>
      <p>Funding extends Anokii to more North Shore communities, each governing its own instance. Costs scale per community; the design and the framework are already built.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="fund-more">
    <p class="fund-more__k">More from this program</p>
    <div class="fund-more__links">
      <a href="/anokii">The Anokii instance</a>
      <a href="/explainers/where-your-data-lives">Where your data lives</a>
      <a href="/support">Support this program</a>
    </div>
  </div>

</article>
